Install openssl in your machine

Open powershell or command prompt as admin and go to the bin location inside installation directory of openssl

Generate a private key:
openssl.exe genrsa -out private.key 2048

Generate CSR from private key :
openssl.exe req -new -key private.key -out request.csr

Generate certificate from private key and CSR.
openssl.exe x509 -req -days 365 -in request.csr -signkey private.key -out certificate.crt


